sp.p:
 In your saucy opinion Sir, and sirrah too; get gone;  
and let this malapert humour return thee no more, for afore  
heaven I will   have  thee tossed in blankets.

 Come do not lode me with volumes of persuasion;  
I am resolved if  she  be gold  she  may abide the taste, let us  
away, I wonder where this wild brother is.

 Neither, I will believe nothing but what trial enforces;  
will you hold your promise for the governing of this  
project with skill, and secrecy?

 The edge of your confidence is well taken off;  
would you not  be  content to withdraw your  
 wager?

 What streams of tears she poured out;  
what tresses of her hair she tore land offered on your supposed  
hearse!

 Well Sir, perhaps I may, if this conclusion take not;  
we will try what operation lies in torture; to pull confession  
from you.
